# ProjectFlo — Migrations & Backfill Scripts

## Prisma migrations
- Workflow: edit `prisma/schema.prisma` → `npx prisma migrate dev --name "kebab-case"` → `npx prisma generate` → test → commit schema + migration folder together.
- Migration names: lowercase kebab-case verb-noun (no `fix`, `changes`, `update`).
- Never hand-edit a migration SQL after it’s been applied to any shared DB.
- One logical change per migration; destructive changes require a two-step deprecate-then-remove flow.

## Squashing migrations (baseline)
- If creating a `0_baseline`, follow the documented diff/resolve process and update `render.yaml` build command to include a safe `prisma migrate resolve --applied 0_baseline || true` before `migrate deploy`.

## Backfill scripts (`packages/backend/scripts/`)
- Naming prefixes: `backfill-*`, `migrate-*`, `seed-*`, `check-*`, `cleanup-*`, `update-*` (match intent).
- All scripts must be idempotent (guard per-record, `upsert` when possible) and log processed vs skipped counts.
- Use raw `PrismaClient` (not NestJS app context).
- Destructive scripts must support a dry-run mode.

